{
  "local_port": 57246,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I apply for PPF?",
  "response": "Applying for a Public Provident Fund (PPF) account in India is a straightforward process. Here's a step-by-step guide to help you:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Determine Where to Open a PPF Account**\nYou can open a PPF account at:\n- **Public Sector Banks** (like SBI, PNB, etc.)\n- **Private Sector Banks** (like ICICI, HDFC, etc.)\n- **Post Offices**\n- **Some authorized branches of financial institutions**\n\n---\n\n### **2. Gather Required Documents**\nYou\u2019ll need the following documents:\n- **Proof of Identity**: Aadhaar card, PAN card, passport, voter ID, or driving license.\n- **Proof of Address**: Aadhaar card, utility bills, rent agreement, or passport.\n- **Passport-sized photographs**\n- **PAN card** (mandatory for deposits exceeding \u20b950,000 annually)\n\n---\n\n### **3. Visit the Bank/Post Office**\n- Visit the nearest bank branch or post office where PPF accounts are opened.\n- Fill out the **PPF Account Opening Form (Form A)**. You can download it online or get it from the branch.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Submit the Form and Documents**\n- Submit the completed form along with the required documents.\n- Pay the **minimum deposit amount** of \u20b9500 to open the account.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Receive Account Details**\n- Once the account is opened, you\u2019ll receive a **PPF passbook** and an account number.\n- The passbook will record all your transactions (deposits, withdrawals, interest earned, etc.).\n\n---\n\n### **6. Online Application (Optional)**\nSome banks allow you to open a PPF account online through their net banking or mobile app. For example:\n- **SBI**: Via the YONO app or internet banking.\n- **ICICI Bank**: Via internet banking.\n\n---\n\n### **7. Start Depositing**\n- You can deposit a minimum of \u20b9500 and a maximum of \u20b91.5 lakh in a financial year.\n- You can deposit in lump sums or in installments (maximum 12 installments per year).\n\n---\n\n### **8. Nominee Details**\n- While opening the account, you can nominate someone by filling out **Form E**.\n\n---\n\n### **Key Points to Remember**\n- PPF accounts have a **lock-in period of 15 years**, with the option to extend in blocks of 5 years.\n- The interest rate is **compounded annually** and is set by the government quarterly.\n- TDS (Tax Deducted at Source) is **not applicable** on PPF.\n\n---\n\nFor more details, you can visit the official website of your bank, post office, or the Ministry of Finance.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
